  "text": "Grafana's three-tier permission model (Viewer/Editor/Admin) is comprehensively defined and enforced across multiple packages:\n\n## Role Definition\n\nThe core role hierarchy is defined in `pkg/apimachinery/identity/role_type.go`, which declares the four role types (RoleNone, RoleViewer, RoleEditor, RoleAdmin) with precedence values (10, 20, 30, 40). The `Includes()` method implements role hierarchy where higher-precedence roles inherit permissions from lower-precedence roles. These are aliased in `pkg/services/org/model.go` for organization-level use.\n\n## Role-to-Permission Mapping\n\nThe role-to-permission mapping is implemented through:\n\n1. **Basic roles** in `pkg/services/accesscontrol/roles.go` via `BuildBasicRoleDefinitions()` - maps organization roles (Viewer, Editor, Admin) to basic RBAC roles\n2. **Fixed roles** registered in `pkg/api/accesscontrol.go` via `declareFixedRoles()` - declares fixed roles and their grants to organization roles (e.g., datasource:reader grants to Admin, datasource:explorer grants to Editor)\n3. **RoleDTO** models in `pkg/services/accesscontrol/models.go` - defines the role structure with permissions and RoleRegistration for granting roles to built-in roles\n\n## Permission Guard Middleware\n\nThe permission enforcement is implemented as middleware:\n\n1. **Main middleware** in `pkg/services/accesscontrol/middleware.go` - `Middleware()` function wraps request handling with permission checks via the `authorize()` function\n2. **Permission evaluation** in `pkg/services/accesscontrol/evaluator.go` - `Evaluator` interface evaluates whether a user has required permissions\n3. **User permission checking** in `pkg/services/accesscontrol/checker.go` - `Checker()` function returns a closure that validates user scopes against required scopes\n4. **Identity role checking** in `pkg/services/authn/identity.go` - `HasRole()` method checks if a user has a specific role (returns true for Grafana Admin or if user's org role includes the required role)\n5. **Access control service** in `pkg/services/accesscontrol/accesscontrol.go` - `ReqHasRole()` provides request-level role checking\n\n## Folder/Dashboard Permission Inheritance\n\nThe folder and dashboard permission hierarchy is implemented through:\n\n1. **Scope inheritance resolver** in `pkg/services/dashboards/accesscontrol.go` - `GetInheritedScopes()` traverses folder hierarchy via `folderService.GetParents()` to collect inherited permissions from parent folders\n2. **Scope resolvers** in `pkg/services/dashboards/accesscontrol.go` - `NewFolderUIDScopeResolver()` and `NewDashboardUIDScopeResolver()` use `GetInheritedScopes()` to include parent folder scopes in permission evaluation\n3. **Three-level permissions** defined in `pkg/services/dashboards/dashboardaccess/dashboard_access.go` - PERMISSION_VIEW, PERMISSION_EDIT, PERMISSION_ADMIN constants map to dashboard/folder operations\n4. **Folder permission service** in `pkg/services/accesscontrol/ossaccesscontrol/folder.go` - `FolderPermissionsService` maps View/Edit/Admin permissions to action sets (FolderViewActions, FolderEditActions, FolderAdminActions) with organization role grants\n5. **Dashboard permission service** in `pkg/services/accesscontrol/ossaccesscontrol/dashboard.go` - `DashboardPermissionsService` similarly maps View/Edit/Admin permissions with action sets that include inherited folder scopes\n6. **Permission APIs** in `pkg/api/folder_permission.go` and `pkg/api/dashboard_permission.go` - provide endpoints to view and update permissions with role mapping (View, Edit, Admin)\n\nThe permission model ensures that Admin users can perform all operations, Editor users can view and edit but not admin, and Viewer users can only view resources. Dashboard and folder permissions inherit from parent folders, creating a hierarchical permission structure where child resources inherit parent permissions unless explicitly overridden."
